    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the salmon is cooked, drizzle your <strong>honey</strong> over and add your <strong>harissa</strong> <strong>paste</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 1 min further or until the sauce is sticky – this is your <strong>harissa & honey salmon</strong></p><p>Transfer the <strong>harissa & honey salmon</strong> to a clean plate</p><p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> boiled water</strong> to the pan and stir it all together until the sauce has loosened a little</p>",
